      • byte2ReferenceEntrySet

        public ObjectSet<Byte2ReferenceMap.Entry<V>> byte2ReferenceEntrySet()
        Description copied from interface: Byte2ReferenceMap
        Returns a type-specific set view of the mappings contained in this map.

        This method is necessary because there is no inheritance along type parameters: it is thus impossible to strengthen Byte2ReferenceMap.entrySet() so that it returns an ObjectSet of type-specific entries (the latter makes it possible to access keys and values with type-specific methods).

        Specified by:
        byte2ReferenceEntrySet in interface Byte2ReferenceMap<V>
        Returns:
        a type-specific set view of the mappings contained in this map.
        See Also:
        Map.entrySet()
